race.comment: VICTORY WIN (4) loves the mile journey here at Doomben with four wins and a second from just six attempts and Maloney stays in the stirrups following that last-start victory here. Drawn to get a cosy run from gate two and should be going very close again. FREE CARRY (7) goes well for rider Lang who has four wins and three placings from just ten steers. Has only missed a drum once in seven starts over this track and trip and can make his presence felt. YET HE MOVES (5) is a three-time winner around this circuit and must be respected out of the champion Waller barn. In the mix. GALIFIANAKIS (2) wasn't too far away when resuming and will have come on with that run now under the belt. One for the multiples. The well-related CABOCHE (1) (half to G3 winner Manolo Blahniq) next in line.
